    # ─── Cyber and online safety (15) ───
    {"id":"sf-x-01","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Phishing — recognise and report",
     "source":"I4C · cybercrime.gov.in","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Red flags: urgent action language, mismatched sender domain, suspicious links, generic greeting, request for OTP/passwords. Never share OTP. Forward suspicious SMS to 1909 (Sancharsaathi reporting), email to phishing@cybercrime.gov.in. Block + report sender."},
    {"id":"sf-x-02","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"OTP fraud — golden-hour reporting",
     "source":"RBI · NPCI · 1930","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"If you shared OTP and money debited: call 1930 (cybercrime) immediately + bank's fraud helpline. Within 24h: lien possible. RBI Zero Liability: no loss if reported within 3 working days; limited liability up to 7 days. Bank reverses if not your fault."},
    {"id":"sf-x-03","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Fake job scam",
     "source":"I4C · Ministry of Labour","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Genuine employers don't ask for registration fee, security deposit, or 'training fee'. Verify on company's official career page. Scan LinkedIn for real employees. Report on cybercrime.gov.in. Particularly common: WFH data-entry, government-job, foreign-job scams."},
    {"id":"sf-x-04","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"SIM swap fraud",
     "source":"DoT · Sancharsaathi","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Fraudster gets duplicate SIM in your name → intercepts OTP. Sudden 'no signal' on phone = warning. Immediately call carrier to block, then bank. Sancharsaathi (sancharsaathi.gov.in) — check all SIMs in your name."},
    {"id":"sf-x-05","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"UPI fraud patterns",
     "source":"NPCI · cybercrime.gov.in","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Common: fake 'received payment' SMS asking you to scan/click to claim refund, OLX/Marketplace QR-scan that's actually a payment request, fake customer-care numbers from Google search. Genuine UPI never asks you to enter PIN to receive."},
    {"id":"sf-x-06","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Sextortion — what to do",
     "source":"I4C · NCW","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Don't pay (they keep coming back). Stop responding. Screenshot evidence. Report at cybercrime.gov.in (women & child special category). Block on all platforms. Family/friend support critical — sextortion thrives on shame isolation."},
    {"id":"sf-x-07","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Revenge porn — IT Act + BNS",
     "source":"IT Act §66E + BNS §77","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Sharing intimate images without consent is criminal. Report: (1) cybercrime.gov.in, (2) FIR under IT Act §66E + BNS §77, (3) take-down request to platform (Instagram, Twitter, etc. — most respond same-day for revenge porn). Save URLs as evidence."},
    {"id":"sf-x-08","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Deepfake nudes — emerging crime",
     "source":"I4C","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"AI-generated nude images using real face. Criminal under IT Act §66E + BNS §75/§77 + obscenity provisions. Report at cybercrime.gov.in. Take-down: file with platform's deepfake policy (Meta, X have specific channels). Specialised lawyers in metros."},
    {"id":"sf-x-09","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Children online — POCSO Section 13-15",
     "source":"POCSO Act 2012 §13-15","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"CSAM (child sexual abuse material) production, transmission, possession — strict liability. Mandatory reporting (§19). Cybertipline at cybercrime.gov.in (women/child) + NCPCR POCSO e-Box. Don't try to investigate — preserve evidence and report."},
    {"id":"sf-x-10","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Cyber bullying — what to do",
     "source":"I4C · UNICEF India","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Save screenshots, URLs, dates. Block on platforms. Don't engage. Tell trusted adult / school counsellor. Report on cybercrime.gov.in. For severe / minor victims: 1098 (Childline). School should activate anti-bullying protocol."},
    {"id":"sf-x-11","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Stalkerware — partner surveillance",
     "source":"Coalition Against Stalkerware","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Apps secretly tracking location, messages, calls. Signs: battery drain, unusual data use, slow phone, app icons you don't recognise. Factory reset removes most (but warn abuser may notice). Domestic violence helpline + safety plan before removal."},
    {"id":"sf-x-12","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Doxxing — protect yourself",
     "source":"DPDP Act 2023 + IT Act","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Sharing of personal info to harass. Remove your details from people-search sites, social media oversharing. Document evidence. Report on cybercrime.gov.in. DPDP Act 2023 gives 'right to erasure' (§12). Filing emergency court protection order possible."},
    {"id":"sf-x-13","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Email account hacked — immediate steps",
     "source":"I4C","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"1) From another device, change password + revoke active sessions. 2) Enable 2FA. 3) Check recovery email/phone — replace if changed. 4) Notify contacts (account may have sent phishing). 5) Bank accounts linked to email — change those passwords too."},
    {"id":"sf-x-14","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Two-factor authentication — set up",
     "source":"NIST 800-63B","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"App-based (Google/Microsoft Authenticator, Authy) > SMS-based (vulnerable to SIM swap) > Hardware key (Yubikey) most secure. Enable for: email, bank, social media, govt portals. Save backup codes offline."},
    {"id":"sf-x-15","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Password best practices",
     "source":"NIST 800-63B","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Unique passwords per site via password manager (Bitwarden, 1Password). 12+ characters, passphrase-style. Never reuse across financial accounts. Check haveibeenpwned.com periodically. Avoid 'security questions' answers that match social-media disclosures."},

    # ─── Physical safety — gendered (15) ───
    {"id":"sf-x-16","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Public transport safety — women",
     "source":"MoHUA · IRCTC","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"GRP helpline 1512 (railways). 139 (general railway). Reserve in ladies' coach/RAC. Avoid empty coaches at night. Share PNR with family. Most metros have CISF — flag distress to nearest officer. Delhi metro Pink panic button."},
    {"id":"sf-x-17","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Auto/cab safety",
     "source":"State transport guidelines","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Share trip on Ola/Uber 'share trip' feature. Verify driver photo + plate before boarding. Sit behind passenger seat for distance. SOS button on app. Pull up at busy spot if anything off — never accept route deviation."},
    {"id":"sf-x-18","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Stalking — what to do",
     "source":"BNS §78 · NCW","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Document every incident with date/time/place + evidence (screenshots, photos). Don't engage. File FIR — stalking is cognizable (BNS §78). For online stalking: cybercrime.gov.in. Request protection order if escalating. Inform workplace, college, neighbours."},
    {"id":"sf-x-19","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Workplace late-night safety",
     "source":"Vishaka guidelines + state Shops Acts","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Employer's duty: safe transport home for women after 8pm (state-specific rules). Maharashtra, Karnataka, TN explicit. If denied: log complaint with labour department. POSH ICC can also rule on commute-time harassment."},
    {"id":"sf-x-20","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Hotel safety — solo traveller",
     "source":"MOT · standard practice","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Stay on floors 4-6 (high enough to deter ground access, low for fire escape). Check door peephole + chain. Bring rubber wedge for door. Don't open for strangers. Tell family your hotel + check-in/out plan. Avoid first-floor rooms."},
    {"id":"sf-x-21","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Voyeurism in hotel/changing rooms",
     "source":"BNS §77 + state hotel safety regs","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Scan for hidden cameras: cover mirrors, look for unusual smoke detectors / clocks / vents. Use phone flashlight in dark — camera lens reflects. Detector apps (limited reliability). Report to hotel + police if found. BNS §77 voyeurism, IT Act §66E for transmission."},
    {"id":"sf-x-22","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Date drug awareness",
     "source":"NIMHANS · medical literature","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"GHB, ketamine, rohypnol — colourless, tasteless. Watch your drink being poured. Never accept drink from stranger. Sudden confusion / drowsiness / memory blank from 1-2 drinks = warning. Medical exam within 12-24h for toxicology + STI/pregnancy."},
    {"id":"sf-x-23","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Acid attack — first response",
     "source":"Laxmi v UoI (2014 SC) · MoHFW","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Immediately flood with water for 15-20 min (NEVER neutralise with chemicals). Remove contaminated clothes. Cover with clean cloth. Rush to hospital — bigger hospital better (burn unit). Free treatment under Burn Care Programme; ₹3 lakh compensation under Victim Compensation Scheme."},
    {"id":"sf-x-24","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Eve-teasing — legal recourse",
     "source":"BNS §75, §79 + IT Act","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Make scene — bystanders intervene if alerted. Photograph offender if safe. FIR under BNS §75 (sexual harassment) or §79 (outraging modesty). 181 (women helpline), 112 (single emergency), 1090 (UP/Rajasthan/Bihar women power line)."},
    {"id":"sf-x-25","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Walking alone safely",
     "source":"Standard safety guidance","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Walk in lit, busy areas. Phone in hand with emergency dial ready. Avoid headphones (situational awareness). Watch shadows in store windows. Vary routes (don't make patterns predictable). Trust gut — cross to other side if uncomfortable."},
    {"id":"sf-x-26","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Self-defence — practical principles",
     "source":"WTC India · Krav Maga","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Best defence: avoid confrontation. If grabbed: aim for eyes, throat, groin, knees. Use voice (loud 'NO', 'HELP'). Run as soon as possible. Real situations rarely look like movie scenes. Brief course (12-20 hours) more useful than belt-grade martial arts."},
    {"id":"sf-x-27","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Safety apps — useful Indian options",
     "source":"App ecosystem","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"112 India app (single emergency, official). Himmat (Delhi Police). bSafe (international, location share + recording). Raksha (private). Safetipin (safe-spot ratings + walks). Key feature to enable: SOS to multiple contacts with location."},
    {"id":"sf-x-28","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Honour-based violence",
     "source":"Shakti Vahini v UoI (2018 SC)","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Khap panchayat-mandated violence is illegal. SC mandated: protection cells in every district, safe houses for inter-faith/inter-caste couples, FIR against family if threats. 24×7 helplines. Special Marriage Act registration entitled to protection."},
    {"id":"sf-x-29","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Trafficking — recognise and report",
     "source":"Anti-Human Trafficking Cell · ITPA 1956","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Red flags: someone under control of another, no IDs/passport on person, scripted answers, fear of speaking, signs of physical abuse. Anti-Human Trafficking Unit in every district (DCP-level). Report: 1098 (children), 181 (women), local police. NHRC for systemic complaints."},
    {"id":"sf-x-30","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"LGBTQ+ safety — discrimination/violence",
     "source":"NALSA judgment + Naz Foundation","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Naz Foundation (Delhi) +91-11-26910499 — counselling, legal. Sahodaran (Chennai/Kerala) — trans women support. Sweekar (NIMHANS) — Indian queer parents. Crime by family/community can be FIR'd under regular criminal sections. Pride NGOs in metros offer support networks."},

    # ─── Medical emergencies (15) ───
    {"id":"sf-x-31","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Heart attack — recognising signs",
     "source":"American Heart Association","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Chest pain/pressure (not always crushing), spreading to jaw/arm/back, sweating, nausea, shortness of breath, sudden weakness. Women, diabetics may have atypical (fatigue, indigestion). Call 108/102/112 immediately. Chew aspirin (300mg) if available and not allergic."},
    {"id":"sf-x-32","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Stroke — FAST signs",
     "source":"American Stroke Association","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"F — Face drooping. A — Arm weakness. S — Speech slurring. T — Time to call 108. Note exact time symptoms started — IV clot-buster window is 4.5 hours from onset. Don't give food/water. Position on side to prevent aspiration."},
    {"id":"sf-x-33","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Choking — adult first aid",
     "source":"American Red Cross","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"5 back blows between shoulder blades + 5 abdominal thrusts (Heimlich) alternately. For pregnant/obese — chest thrusts. If victim unconscious: CPR. Pregnancy + late stage: anti-fundal compressions only."},
    {"id":"sf-x-34","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"CPR — adult",
     "source":"American Heart Association 2020","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"30 chest compressions + 2 rescue breaths. Compress 5-6 cm deep at 100-120/min (Bee Gees 'Stayin' Alive' tempo). Hands-only CPR also acceptable for untrained. Continue till AED arrives or victim revives or you're physically exhausted."},
    {"id":"sf-x-35","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Anaphylaxis (severe allergy)",
     "source":"WAO","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Swelling of lips/tongue/throat, hives, breathing difficulty, drop in BP, dizziness. Inject epinephrine (EpiPen) if available. Call 108 + lie flat with legs raised. May need second dose in 5-15 min. Don't try to eat/drink."},
    {"id":"sf-x-36","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Seizure — what to do",
     "source":"Epilepsy Foundation India","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Don't restrain. Don't put anything in mouth. Move sharp objects away. Cushion head. Time the seizure — call 108 if > 5 min, second seizure, or first-ever. Turn to recovery position after. Stay with person till fully alert."},
    {"id":"sf-x-37","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Hypoglycemia (low blood sugar) emergency",
     "source":"Diabetes UK · ADA","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Sweating, shakiness, confusion, slurred speech, fainting. Give 15g fast-acting sugar (glucose tablets, juice, sugar dissolved in water). Recheck in 15 min. If unconscious: don't force-feed. Glucagon injection if available. Call 108."},
    {"id":"sf-x-38","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Burn — first aid",
     "source":"AIIMS Burns Unit","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Cool with running water 20 min. Remove jewellery (before swelling). Cover with clean cloth (NOT cotton wool, ice, oil, toothpaste). For chemical burns: flush 15-20 min. Hospital for: > palm-size, face/hands/feet/genitals, deep burns, electrical/chemical."},
    {"id":"sf-x-39","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Bleeding — control",
     "source":"American Red Cross","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Direct pressure with clean cloth 10-15 min. Elevate above heart if possible. Don't remove embedded objects. Tourniquet only if life-threatening + first aid trained. Call 108 if: spurting, won't stop, deep, large surface, eyes."},
    {"id":"sf-x-40","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Drowning rescue",
     "source":"WHO drowning prevention","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Reach (with stick/rope), throw (rope/floating object) — don't go in unless trained. Get victim out. If not breathing: CPR (5 rescue breaths first for drowning). Even revived person needs hospital — secondary drowning possible 1-24h later."},
    {"id":"sf-x-41","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Heat stroke",
     "source":"NDMA heat action plan","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Body temp > 40°C, confusion, dry skin (heat stroke) vs wet skin (heat exhaustion). Move to shade, cool with water/wet cloths, fan. Don't force water if unconscious. Call 108 — heat stroke is medical emergency, mortality if untreated."},
    {"id":"sf-x-42","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Hypothermia",
     "source":"NDMA · WHO","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Shivering (early), confusion, slurred speech, slow breathing, drowsiness, loss of shivering (severe). Remove wet clothing, wrap in warm blankets, warm drink (if conscious). Don't apply direct heat to extremities. Call 108. Heart rhythm fragile — gentle handling."},
    {"id":"sf-x-43","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Snakebite — first aid",
     "source":"ICMR snakebite management 2024","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"DON'T cut, suck, apply tourniquet, or ice. Do: keep calm, immobilise bite area below heart level, remove tight clothing/jewellery, get to hospital with ASV (anti-snake venom). Photograph snake if safe — don't try to catch. India has 'Big Four': cobra, krait, viper, saw-scaled viper."},
    {"id":"sf-x-44","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Dog bite — rabies prophylaxis",
     "source":"WHO PEP guidelines","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Wash wound 15 min with soap + running water. Apply antiseptic. Visit hospital for PEP (post-exposure prophylaxis) within 24h — Category III bites (deep, bleeding) need both vaccine + immunoglobulin. Vaccination schedule: 5 doses over 28 days OR 4-dose Essen schedule."},
    {"id":"sf-x-45","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Scorpion sting",
     "source":"MoHFW","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Most Indian scorpion stings — local pain, swelling, manage with cold compress + paracetamol. Red flags (Indian red scorpion — Mahabaleshwar / Konkan / coastal): vomiting, sweating, breathing difficulty — hospital + prazosin treatment. Don't apply ice or cut."},

    # ─── Disaster preparedness (10) ───
    {"id":"sf-x-46","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Earthquake — during shaking",
     "source":"NDMA","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Drop, Cover, Hold. Get under sturdy table; protect head. Stay away from windows + tall furniture. If outdoors: open area, away from buildings/wires. If driving: pull over, stay in vehicle. Most injuries: falling objects, not building collapse."},
    {"id":"sf-x-47","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Earthquake — after shaking",
     "source":"NDMA","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Check for injuries — first aid. Check gas/water/electrical lines. Don't use lifts. Aftershocks possible — leave damaged buildings. Have go-bag (water, ID, medicines, torch, radio, cash). NDRF helpline 011-23438252 / 011-23438253."},
    {"id":"sf-x-48","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Flood — before, during, after",
     "source":"NDMA flood guidelines","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Before: identify higher ground, prepare go-bag. During: turn off gas/electricity, evacuate if advised, never walk/drive through floodwater (6 inches can knock you down, 12 inches floats a car). After: don't return till officials clear, watch for snakes/contamination."},
    {"id":"sf-x-49","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Cyclone preparation",
     "source":"NDMA cyclone shelter","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Follow IMD warnings (cyclone alert 48h before, warning 24h, post-landfall watches). Secure loose objects, tape windows. Stock 3 days' water/food. Charge phones + power banks. Evacuate to designated shelter if Category 3+. Stay indoors during eye-of-storm calm (deceptive)."},
    {"id":"sf-x-50","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Landslide warning signs",
     "source":"NDMA landslide guidelines","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Cracks in walls/ground, tilting trees, sudden change in water flow, unusual sounds. Common in Himalayas, Western Ghats, NE during monsoon. Evacuate up-slope perpendicular to landslide path (not down). Cars/houses on slope at higher risk."},
    {"id":"sf-x-51","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Fire — apartment building",
     "source":"NDMA fire safety","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Hear alarm → check door (warm = fire on other side, use alternate exit). Crawl below smoke. Stairs not lift. If trapped: signal from window, seal door cracks with wet cloth, call 101 + give location. Yearly check: extinguishers, smoke alarms, exit routes."},
    {"id":"sf-x-52","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Fire — kitchen fire",
     "source":"NDMA","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"DON'T pour water on oil fire — explodes. Turn off heat, cover with metal lid (smothers oxygen). Class K extinguisher for restaurants. LPG fire: turn off cylinder valve, evacuate, call 101 + cylinder supplier."},
    {"id":"sf-x-53","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Lightning safety",
     "source":"NDMA · IMD","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"30-30 rule: if thunder follows lightning within 30 sec, take shelter; wait 30 min after last thunder before going out. Avoid open fields, water bodies, isolated tall trees. Damodar Valley app gives lightning forecasts. Most lightning deaths in India: outdoor farm workers."},
    {"id":"sf-x-54","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Tsunami warning",
     "source":"INCOIS","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Strong earthquake near coast + ocean recedes suddenly = tsunami warning signs. Move to higher ground (10m+) immediately, away from coast. Don't return for 2-3h after first wave. INCOIS (incois.gov.in) sends warnings via SMS in coastal areas."},
    {"id":"sf-x-55","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Go-bag essentials",
     "source":"NDMA disaster preparedness","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"3-day water (4L/person/day), non-perishable food, ID copies in waterproof bag, cash, torch + batteries, first aid kit, prescription medicines, hand-crank radio, whistle, multi-tool, mobile charger + power bank, masks, contact list on paper."},

    # ─── Children & elder safety (10) ───
    {"id":"sf-x-56","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Childline 1098",
     "source":"MWCD · childlineindia.org","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"24×7 emergency helpline for children in distress (abuse, missing, abandoned, runaway, trafficking, exploitation). Pan-India. NGO-staffed but government-supported. Free calls. Coordinates with police, hospital, CWC (Child Welfare Committee)."},
    {"id":"sf-x-57","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"POCSO e-Box reporting",
     "source":"NCPCR pocsoebox.nic.in","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Online platform for children/anyone to report sexual abuse. Anonymous reporting possible. Auto-routed to relevant authorities. NCPCR follows up. Useful when local police inaccessible or distrusted."},
    {"id":"sf-x-58","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Body safety — teaching children",
     "source":"NCPCR · Arpan Foundation","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Age-appropriate: correct body part names, 'safe vs unsafe touch', 'no secret is more important than your safety', trusted adult identification (mom + 2 others), 'tell-tell-tell' until believed. Arpan free workshops in schools."},
    {"id":"sf-x-59","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Missing child — first 24 hours",
     "source":"Trackchild.gov.in","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Immediately call 1098, 112, file FIR (no waiting period for child missing). Upload photo + details to trackchild.gov.in. AHTU (Anti-Human Trafficking Unit) gets alerted. Recent photo + clothing description critical."},
    {"id":"sf-x-60","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Bullying at school — escalation",
     "source":"NCPCR · UNICEF","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Document incidents (dates, witnesses, injuries). Inform class teacher → principal in writing. If not resolved: District Education Officer → State Commission for Protection of Child Rights → NCPCR. Severe physical bullying = FIR under BNS."},
    {"id":"sf-x-61","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Online child safety — controls",
     "source":"NCPCR · I4C","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Parental controls: Google Family Link, Apple Screen Time, YouTube Kids. Talk openly about online risks without scaring. Phone use in common areas. Age-appropriate platforms (no Instagram <13). Report CSAM at cybertipline.com or cybercrime.gov.in."},
    {"id":"sf-x-62","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Elder abuse — recognise",
     "source":"HelpAge India","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Physical (bruises), emotional (intimidation), financial (asset transfers under coercion), neglect (poor hygiene, untreated medical), abandonment. Reporter: anyone — Elderline 14567, MWPSC Act tribunal, police FIR for criminal acts."},
    {"id":"sf-x-63","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Senior citizen home safety",
     "source":"AIIMS Geriatric · HelpAge","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Fall-proof: anti-slip mats in bathroom, grab bars, adequate lighting (especially night). Medical alert button. Trusted neighbour with key. Police senior-citizen registration (most metros' Senior Citizen Cell) — periodic well-being checks."},
    {"id":"sf-x-64","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Elder financial fraud — common scams",
     "source":"HelpAge · I4C","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Common targets: lottery wins, fake government refund, KBC selection, fake grandson in trouble (deepfake), property reverification fraud. Bank account-mate check periodically. SBI Pensioners' helpline + ICICI Senior Care for verification."},
    {"id":"sf-x-65","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Dementia patient safety",
     "source":"ARDSI · NIMHANS","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"ID bracelet with name/phone/'memory loss — please call family'. GPS tracker (Apple AirTag in wallet). Door alarms / locks high or low (out of usual sight line). Lock kitchen knives, gas. ARDSI (alzheimerindia.org) helpline + support groups."},

    # ─── Vehicle/road safety (10) ───
    {"id":"sf-x-66","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Road accident — Good Samaritan rights",
     "source":"MV Act §134A (2019)","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Helping accident victim — no civil/criminal liability for actions taken in good faith. Cannot be detained at hospital. Don't have to disclose identity. Hospital must give 'cashless treatment' for first hour (golden hour). Call 108 + 112."},
    {"id":"sf-x-67","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Hit and run — compensation",
     "source":"MV Act §161-163A","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Solatium scheme: ₹2 lakh (death), ₹50,000 (grievous injury) regardless of who's at fault, even if perpetrator untraced. Apply to Claims Tribunal. Cashless treatment under MV Act 2019 within golden hour at empanelled hospital."},
    {"id":"sf-x-68","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Two-wheeler safety essentials",
     "source":"MoRTH · ISI BIS standards","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"ISI-marked full-face helmet (both rider + pillion mandatory). Avoid mobile while riding (e-challan + cancellation risk). Riding kit (jacket + gloves + boots) saves life in accidents. Reflective vest for night. Don't carry > 1 pillion (illegal beyond)."},
    {"id":"sf-x-69","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Drunk driving — limits and penalties",
     "source":"MV Act §185","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"BAC limit 30 mg / 100 ml blood (~one small beer). First offence: ₹10,000 fine + 6 months jail. Second offence: ₹15,000 + 2 years jail + 1 year licence suspension. Insurance becomes void for accidents under influence."},
    {"id":"sf-x-70","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Long-distance driving safety",
     "source":"NHAI · road safety guidelines","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"15-min break every 2 hours. Don't drive 2-5 am (drowsy peak). Stop at NHAI restaurants/petrol pumps (lit, monitored). 112 + 1033 (NHAI emergency for highway issues). Fuel up at ≥ ¼ tank. Cash + phone power bank."},
    {"id":"sf-x-71","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Vehicle breakdown — at night",
     "source":"NHAI emergency","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Pull to leftmost shoulder. Turn on hazard lights. Place reflective triangles 30-50m behind. Stay inside vehicle (safer than outside on highway). Call 1033 (NHAI) or 112. If stranger offers help: thank, but ask them to call official services."},
    {"id":"sf-x-72","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Documents to carry while driving",
     "source":"MV Act § 130","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Mandatory: driving licence, RC, valid insurance, PUC. Digital copies on DigiLocker / mParivahan acceptable since 2018. Permit (for commercial vehicles). Vehicle fitness certificate (for older vehicles)."},
    {"id":"sf-x-73","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Insurance claim after accident",
     "source":"IRDAI · IIBI","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Within 48 hours of accident: FIR (mandatory for big claims), informed insurer. Photos of damage. Surveyor inspection. Cashless (network garage) or reimbursement. Third-party injury/death — separate claim under MV Act."},
    {"id":"sf-x-74","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"E-challan check + payment",
     "source":"echallan.parivahan.gov.in","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Check pending challans by vehicle number / DL. Pay online. Disputed: contest at virtual court for traffic violations. Unpaid old challans now block fitness/insurance renewal in many states."},
    {"id":"sf-x-75","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Child car seat — legal requirement",
     "source":"MoRTH 2022 amendment","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"From 2022: children under 4 must use child restraint (car seat) on motorcycle (limit 40 km/h, helmet from age 4) AND on passenger cars. Rear-facing infant seat 0-2, forward facing 2-4, booster 4-12 ideally."},

    # ─── Hindi safety chunks (10) ───
    {"id":"sf-x-76","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"पैसा साइबर ठगी से वापस — golden hour (Hindi)",
     "source":"1930 · cybercrime.gov.in","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"OTP देने / ठगी होने के तुरंत बाद: (1) 1930 पर कॉल करें, (2) cybercrime.gov.in पर ऑनलाइन शिकायत, (3) बैंक के fraud helpline पर भी। 1 घंटे के अंदर रिपोर्ट करें — पैसा वापस होने की संभावना सबसे ज़्यादा।"},
    {"id":"sf-x-77","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"महिला हिंसा — तुरंत मदद (Hindi)",
     "source":"NCW · 181 · 112","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"तुरंत मदद: 112 (पूरे देश आपातकाल), 181 (महिला हेल्पलाइन), 1090 (UP/राजस्थान/बिहार महिला पावरलाइन), NCW 7827170170। हर ज़िले में One Stop Centre (सखी) — medical + legal + counselling + 5 दिन की शरण।"},
    {"id":"sf-x-78","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"बच्चे के साथ ज़्यादती की शिकायत (Hindi)",
     "source":"1098 · POCSO e-Box","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"बच्चे को कोई भी ज़्यादती — 1098 (Childline 24×7), pocsoebox.nic.in पर ऑनलाइन, सबसे पास के पुलिस स्टेशन में FIR। POCSO Act के तहत reporting अनिवार्य — हर adult की कानूनी ज़िम्मेदारी। बच्चे की पहचान सुरक्षित रहती है।"},
    {"id":"sf-x-79","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"दिल का दौरा — पहचान (Hindi)",
     "source":"American Heart Association","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"छाती में दर्द/दबाव (हमेशा severe नहीं), जबड़े/हाथ/पीठ तक फैले, पसीना, मतली, साँस फूलना। महिलाओं/मधुमेह वालों में अलग — थकान, अपच। तुरंत 108 या 102 पर कॉल। 300mg एस्पिरिन चबाएँ (अगर allergy नहीं)।"},
    {"id":"sf-x-80","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"साँप काटे तो (Hindi)",
     "source":"ICMR snakebite management 2024","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"न करें: काटना, चूसना, tourniquet, बर्फ। करें: शांत रहें, घाव वाले हिस्से को दिल से नीचे रखें, tight कपड़े/जेवर हटाएँ, ASV (anti-snake venom) वाले अस्पताल पहुँचें। साँप को पकड़ने की कोशिश न करें — फोटो काफी है।"},
    {"id":"sf-x-81","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"घर में आग — क्या करें (Hindi)",
     "source":"NDMA fire safety","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"धुएँ के नीचे रेंगकर निकलें। सीढ़ी का प्रयोग, lift नहीं। दरवाज़ा गर्म है तो दूसरा रास्ता। फँस गए तो: खिड़की से signal, गीले कपड़े से दरवाज़े की दरारें बंद करें, 101 पर कॉल + अपनी सटीक location बताएँ।"},
    {"id":"sf-x-82","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"भूकंप के दौरान (Hindi)",
     "source":"NDMA","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Drop-Cover-Hold: मज़बूत मेज़ के नीचे जाएँ, सिर बचाएँ। खिड़कियाँ + बड़े फर्नीचर से दूर। बाहर: खुली जगह, बिल्डिंग/तार से दूर। गाड़ी में: रोककर अंदर रहें। अधिकांश चोटें — गिरती चीज़ों से, न कि बिल्डिंग गिरने से।"},
    {"id":"sf-x-83","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"बुज़ुर्ग शोषण — हेल्पलाइन (Hindi)",
     "source":"HelpAge India · Elderline 14567","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"शारीरिक/मानसिक/आर्थिक शोषण, उपेक्षा, संपत्ति हड़पना — Elderline 14567 पर कॉल। MWPSC Act 2007 के तहत SDM के सामने tribunal में आवेदन। बच्चों से ₹10,000/माह तक maintenance का अधिकार।"},
    {"id":"sf-x-84","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"सड़क दुर्घटना में मदद — Good Samaritan (Hindi)",
     "source":"MV Act §134A","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"घायल को अस्पताल पहुँचाने पर कोई civil/criminal ज़िम्मेदारी नहीं — Good Samaritan कानून आपको सुरक्षित करता है। अस्पताल पर 'golden hour' में cashless इलाज देने की ज़िम्मेदारी। 108 + 112 पर तुरंत कॉल।"},
    {"id":"sf-x-85","domain":"Safety","lang":"hi","topic":"भारत के सभी emergency नंबर (Hindi)",
     "source":"MHA · All emergency directories","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"112 (single emergency), 100 (police), 101 (fire), 102/108 (ambulance), 1091 (महिला), 1098 (बच्चे), 1930 (साइबर ठगी), 1078 (आपदा), 1077 (राज्य आपदा), 14416 (Tele-MANAS मानसिक स्वास्थ्य), 14567 (Elderline)।"},

    # ─── German safety (5) ───
    {"id":"sf-x-86","domain":"Safety","lang":"de","topic":"Erste Hilfe Herzinfarkt (German)",
     "source":"Deutsche Herzstiftung","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Plötzlicher Brustdruck, Ausstrahlung in Arm/Kiefer/Rücken, Schweißausbruch, Atemnot. Sofort 112 anrufen. Bei Bewusstlosigkeit + keine Atmung: Herzdruckmassage (100-120/min) bis Rettungsdienst kommt."},
    {"id":"sf-x-87","domain":"Safety","lang":"de","topic":"Brandfall im Wohnhaus (German)",
     "source":"Deutscher Feuerwehrverband","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Wohnung verlassen, Tür schließen (verzögert Rauchausbreitung). Keinen Aufzug. Wenn Rauch im Flur: Wohnung als Schutzraum nutzen, nasse Tücher in Türritzen, Fenster öffnen + sich bemerkbar machen. 112 anrufen, Standort durchgeben."},
    {"id":"sf-x-88","domain":"Safety","lang":"de","topic":"Häusliche Gewalt — Akute Hilfe (German)",
     "source":"Hilfetelefon","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Hilfetelefon Gewalt gegen Frauen 08000 116 016 (24/7, 17 Sprachen + Gebärdensprache). Polizei 110. Frauenhaus über frauenhauskoordinierung.de finden. Gewaltschutzambulanz für Spurensicherung ohne Anzeigepflicht."},
    {"id":"sf-x-89","domain":"Safety","lang":"de","topic":"Kindesmissbrauch melden (German)",
     "source":"Hilfeportal Sexueller Missbrauch","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"N.I.N.A. e.V. 0800 22 55 530 (kostenlos, anonym). Hilfetelefon Sexueller Missbrauch 0800 22 55 530. Bei akuter Gefahr 110. Jugendamt zuständig für Inobhutnahme. Schule + Ärzte haben Meldewege."},
    {"id":"sf-x-90","domain":"Safety","lang":"de","topic":"Cybercrime in Deutschland melden (German)",
     "source":"BKA Cybercrime","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Bei Phishing/Betrug: Online-Wache der Landespolizei nutzen. Bei Identitätsdiebstahl: Beweise sichern (Screenshots), Konten sperren, Strafanzeige. Verbraucherzentrale berät zu Internetbetrug. BSI Bürger-CERT informiert über aktuelle Bedrohungen."},

    # ─── More safety misc (10) ───
    {"id":"sf-x-91","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Mental-health crisis at home — what to do",
     "source":"NIMHANS · iCall","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Person threatening self-harm: stay calm, remove access to means (medications, sharp objects). Don't argue or moralise. Call iCall 9152987821, Vandrevala 1860-2662-345, Tele-MANAS 14416. Active danger: 112 + nearest psychiatric ER. Don't leave alone if actively suicidal."},
    {"id":"sf-x-92","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Building collapse — survival",
     "source":"NDRF","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"During tremor: drop-cover-hold. After: don't move heavy debris from yourself — wait for trained rescue. Conserve breath (cover nose/mouth with cloth). Tap on pipe/wall (audible across debris). NDRF mobilises for major incidents."},
    {"id":"sf-x-93","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Active shooter / attack — civilian response",
     "source":"NDMA","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Run (if safe exit), Hide (lock + barricade + silence devices), Fight (last resort, with whatever is available). Call 112 only when safe. India relatively rare but Mumbai 26/11 + Pulwama showed need for civilian protocols."},
    {"id":"sf-x-94","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Gas leak at home — LPG",
     "source":"PNGRB","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"DON'T switch lights / fans / electrical (spark = explosion). Open windows. Turn off cylinder valve. Evacuate. Call gas distributor + fire 101. Test for leaks: soap-water on joints (bubbles = leak). Replace regulator periodically."},
    {"id":"sf-x-95","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Carbon monoxide poisoning",
     "source":"CDC · MoHFW","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Generators, gas heaters, charcoal indoors → odourless CO. Symptoms: headache, dizziness, nausea, confusion, weakness — multiple people affected simultaneously = red flag. Move to fresh air immediately, 100% O2 in hospital. Install CO detector if using gas appliances."},
    {"id":"sf-x-96","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Suspicious package — bomb threat",
     "source":"NSG · Mumbai Police","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Don't touch, move, open. Clear area 100m+. Call 112 + nearest police. Bomb Disposal Squad responds. Note: time + sender + appearance + smell. Most public-place suspicious packages are false alarms; treat as real till cleared."},
    {"id":"sf-x-97","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Wildlife encounter — leopard / wild boar",
     "source":"WII · State Forest Departments","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Don't run — provokes chase. Make yourself large, slow back away. Make noise (loud, deep voice). Carry torch at night (eye-shine alerts). Keep children/pets close. Report to State Forest Helpline (1926 most states). Don't kill — punishable under WLPA 1972."},
    {"id":"sf-x-98","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Lost passport abroad — Indian missions",
     "source":"MEA · Indian Embassies","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"Police report (FIR) locally. Indian Embassy/Consulate for Emergency Certificate (travel home) or new passport. Documents: photo, FIR copy, fare receipts, any ID copies. mPassport Seva app for nearest embassy contact. 24×7 helpline at most missions."},
    {"id":"sf-x-99","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"NRI in trouble — Indian government help",
     "source":"MEA · MADAD portal","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"madad.gov.in for grievance registration. Indian community welfare schemes for distressed (esp Gulf workers). Emergency repatriation, legal help, mortal remains transport. Local Indian Embassy first contact. Call 1800-11-3090 (Foreign Office)."},
    {"id":"sf-x-100","domain":"Safety","lang":"en","topic":"Drowning in pond/river — village context",
     "source":"WHO drowning prevention 2021","lastVerifiedOn":"2025-10-15","verifiedBy":"human",
     "text":"India 1.5 lakh drownings/year — most in ponds/wells, rural, monsoon. Reach with stick/rope first. Throw float. Don't jump unless trained (rescuer often becomes second victim). Out of water + not breathing: CPR (5 rescue breaths first, then 30 compressions cycles)."},

